</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dVNjXY jGYlKM pf-67_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-68_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regular training sessions</strong> - Organise regular resuscitation training sessions for staff, ensuring they are competent and confident in their abilities.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-70_ pf-text-1"><strong>Invest in equipment </strong>- Invest in quality equipment, such as AEDs, and ensure they are strategically placed for rapid access during emergencies.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-72_ pf-text-1"><strong>Integration with clinical governance</strong> - Incorporate resuscitation training into broader clinical governance frameworks to ensure ongoing quality improvement and compliance with regulatory standards.



































































